[
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "Exam structure:",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "The test will be 3 hours, on paper, in person on campus.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "This test will be sat by students who have already received a credit, i.e. 65% of the unit. The objective of this",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "test is to distinguish between students who should receive:",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  A credit - they should score 0-4 on this test",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  A distinction - they should score 5-14 on this test",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  A high distinction -they should score 15-35 on this test",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "As you can see, more than half of the marks on the test should only be obtained by students who are at a high",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "distinction level. As a consequence, you can expect the easiest questions on the test to be challenging, and the",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "hardest questions to be very hard. It is likely that some students who attempt the test will receive very few",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "marks.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "Another way to say this is that you \"only\" need 43% on this test to get an HD. So you should not expect to feel",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "the same way walking out of this test as a typical exam, i.e. that you only did well if you answered most",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "questions.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "With this in mind, it is important to remember that you have done very well to be sitting this test at all! This is a",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "difficult unit, and if you are sitting this test, you have already passed and received a credit. Given that you have",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "made it this far, you might as well give it your best shot and see how you go.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "Test structure",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "Section 1 - 10 marks",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  10 questions each worth 1 mark.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  Assess your ability to answer simple definition/justification type questions about the content.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  Answers will be short, 1-3 sentences (sometimes just a number or formula)",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "Inaccurate or vague answers will receive 0, clear and correct answers will receive 1.",
    "bold": true
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "Section 2 - 10 marks",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  5 questions each worth 2 marks.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  Assess your ability to apply your understanding of the content.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  Proofs or problems solving questions",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  Clearly related to a concept/topic from the unit",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  Answers will be 3-5 sentences",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  Partial marks (i.e. 1 mark out of 2) are possible for answers with the right idea but some issue",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "Section 3 - 15 marks",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  3 questions each worth 5 marks",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  More than 3 questions will be provided",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  You must choose which three you answer",
    "bold": true
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  Assess your ability to solve novel problems using concepts/algorithms taught in this unit.",
    "bold": true
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "\u25cf  Partial marks are possible",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "It may not be initially clear how to solve these problems!",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "If you answer more than 3, we will mark 3 at random. We will not look at the fourth submission at all",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "Time",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "It is vital to spend a few minutes reading the whole test before starting to work. You probably should not work",
    "bold": true
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "through the test from the front to the back, but rather in order of questions that you are confident you can",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "answer well.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "Remember that you only need 5 marks for a distinction! You can find those 5 marks anywhere in the test,",
    "bold": true
  },
  {
    "page": 1,
    "text": "they might not be on the first 5 questions.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "The test runs for 3 hours and has 35 marks. That said, we do not expect all the marks to take the same amount",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "of time. How long it takes to do 1 mark worth of work depends on your skillset, but in general the earlier marks",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "will take less time.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "Logistic",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "To be announced closer to the date, once we have the full list of students who will be sitting for it after the",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "Week-14 PTs.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "Some very important notes on the list of practice questions",
    "bold": true
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "1.  Questions are listed with a section. This does not mean the question is of the correct difficulty for that",
    "bold": true
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "section, some may be far easier. This does not mean the question is of the type that would be found in",
    "bold": true
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "that section. What it means is that it requires skills or knowledge that would be tested in that section.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "2.  We have included most questions that we thought were relevant to the D/HD test. The questions in the",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "applied sheets do not cover every topic equally, so there may be more questions than you might need",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "on some topics. You should not proceed through the list from front to back, but in an order that makes",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "sense to you based on your skills.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "3.  Many questions on the applied sheets are more open ended than questions on the test will be, as they",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "are designed for a discussion based context. In order to help you prepare for the test, we recommend",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "that you",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "1.  Determine the complexity of every algorithm you create while answering questions",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "2.  Justify/prove every claim that you make to yourself while answering questions",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "text": "The questions in bold are a suggestion for questions that cover key ideas very well.",
    "bold": false
  },
  {
